[DhtmlXQ_comment20]E3+5 could also be played to keep the game in a standoff state.[/DhtmlXQ_comment20]
[DhtmlXQ_comment32]A rather even game.||In summary: ||in this opening, it is easy to reach a standoff. ||The ability to deploy your pieces to slowly gain the lead is perhaps the most crucial factor and it is the only way to win. ||As compared to some of the earlier, more aggressive variations, in this variation, the ability to read the game and make more long term plans is perhaps more important.[/DhtmlXQ_comment32]
